2026-04-21 02:41:41 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1', 'Control Module 2', 'Control Module 3', 'Control Module 4', 'Control Module 5', 'Control Module 6', 'Control Module 7', 'Control Module 8'] hypothesis_explanation='The indicator LEDs in all 8 control modules are missing (removed physically). In this circuit, these LEDs with their resistors are in parallel to the switch but in series with the load path. Their absence results in an open circuit inside every module (the LED/resistor path is the only path across the switch terminals). With all 8 control modules missing their LEDs, the entire series circuit between the power supply and the load is open at every control module, preventing current from reaching the lamp. This is why none of the switch indicators light up and the lamp does not turn on, despite normal power supply operation.'
